-- Arrays
('CODING','Given an array of integers, find the maximum subarray sum (Kadane''s Algorithm).','','The maximum subarray sum can be found by maintaining a running sum and resetting when it goes negative. Time: O(n), Space: O(1).','Use Kadane''s algorithm: maxSoFar = arr[0]; maxEndingHere = arr[0]; for i in 1..n: maxEndingHere = max(arr[i], maxEndingHere+arr[i]); maxSoFar = max(maxSoFar, maxEndingHere);','Medium','Arrays','Amazon','Any',1),
('CODING','Find the two numbers in an array that add up to a target sum.','','Use a hash set. For each element x, check if (target-x) is in the set. Time: O(n).','HashMap approach: iterate array, for each num check if complement exists in map, else add num to map.','Easy','Arrays','Google','Any',1),
('CODING','Rotate an array to the right by k steps.','','Reverse entire array, then reverse first k elements, then reverse the rest. Time: O(n), Space: O(1).','Three-step reverse: reverse(0,n-1), reverse(0,k-1), reverse(k,n-1).','Easy','Arrays','Microsoft','Any',1),
('CODING','Find the product of all elements except self without using division.','','Use prefix and suffix products. Two passes: left product array then multiply right products. Time: O(n), Space: O(n).','Left pass: res[i] = product of all elements left of i. Right pass: multiply res[i] by running product from right.','Medium','Arrays','Facebook','Any',1),
('CODING','Merge two sorted arrays into one sorted array.','','Use two pointers, compare and merge. Time: O(m+n), Space: O(m+n).','Two pointer approach: i=0, j=0, compare arr1[i] and arr2[j], append smaller, advance pointer.','Easy','Arrays','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Find the missing number in an array containing 1 to n.','','Expected sum = n*(n+1)/2. Subtract actual sum. Or XOR all with 1..n.','Sum formula: n*(n+1)/2 - sum(array). XOR method: xor all elements and all 1..n, result is missing.','Easy','Arrays','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Find the duplicate number in an array of n+1 integers where each is between 1 and n.','','Floyd''s cycle detection or sum formula. Without modifying array: fast-slow pointer.','Floyd cycle: treat array as linked list where arr[i] points to arr[arr[i]]. Find cycle entry = duplicate.','Hard','Arrays','Google','Any',1),
('CODING','Find the longest consecutive sequence in an unsorted array.','','Use a HashSet. For each number that is a start (n-1 not in set), count consecutive streak. O(n) time.','Add all to set. For each num, if num-1 not in set it''s a sequence start. Count streak forwards.','Medium','Arrays','Google','Any',1),
('CODING','Move all zeros to the end of an array while maintaining relative order of non-zero elements.','','Two pointer: maintain a write pointer for non-zero elements, then fill rest with zeros.','Write pointer approach: copy non-zeros in place, fill remaining positions with 0.','Easy','Arrays','Facebook','Any',1),
('CODING','Find the intersection of two arrays.','','Use a HashSet from first array. Iterate second, collect matches. For duplicates use HashMap with counts.','HashSet of arr1, iterate arr2 checking set. For count-aware: use HashMap storing frequencies.','Easy','Arrays','Any',NULL,1),

-- Strings
('CODING','Check if a string is a palindrome (ignore case and non-alphanumeric).','','Two pointer approach: left and right, skip non-alphanumeric, compare lowercase. O(n).','while left < right: skip non-alnum, compare lower(s[left]) == lower(s[right]), advance pointers.','Easy','Strings','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Find the longest substring without repeating characters.','','Sliding window with HashMap storing last seen index. Expand right, shrink left on repeat. O(n).','Sliding window: use map of char->last_index. Window start = max(start, map[char]+1) on duplicate.','Medium','Strings','Amazon','Any',1),
('CODING','Check if two strings are anagrams of each other.','','Sort both and compare, or use frequency count array of 26 letters. O(n) time.','Count chars in s, subtract for t. If all zero, anagram. Or sort both strings and compare.','Easy','Strings','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Find all anagrams of a pattern in a string.','','Sliding window with frequency maps. Compare window frequency with pattern frequency. O(n).','Fixed-size window equal to pattern length. Slide and compare frequency arrays.','Medium','Strings','Google','Any',1),
('CODING','Implement strStr() - find first occurrence of needle in haystack.','','Naive O(nm) or KMP O(n+m). KMP builds failure function from pattern then matches.','KMP: build LPS array from pattern. Use LPS to skip unnecessary comparisons during match.','Medium','Strings','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Reverse words in a sentence.','','Split by spaces, reverse the list of words, join. Handle multiple spaces.','s.split(" ") -> filter empty -> reverse -> join with single space.','Easy','Strings','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Find the longest common prefix of an array of strings.','','Sort strings, compare first and last. The common prefix of first and last is LCP of all.','Sort array. Compare s[0] and s[last] character by character until mismatch.','Easy','Strings','Google','Any',1),
('CODING','Count and say sequence - given n, generate the nth term.','','Iterate n times. For each term, count consecutive same digits and say.','Start with "1". Each iteration: scan and count runs, build next string.','Easy','Strings','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Check if a string has balanced parentheses.','','Use a stack. Push open brackets, on close check if top matches. Empty stack at end = balanced.','Stack approach: push on open, pop-and-check on close. Valid if stack empty at end.','Easy','Strings','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Find the minimum window substring that contains all characters of pattern T.','','Sliding window with two pointers. Expand right, contract left when window valid. O(n).','Track char frequencies needed. Expand r until all chars covered, then shrink l to minimize.','Hard','Strings','Google','Any',1),

-- Linked List
('CODING','Reverse a linked list in place.','','Iterative: prev=null, cur=head. While cur: next=cur.next; cur.next=prev; prev=cur; cur=next.','Three pointer approach iteratively. Recursive: reverse(head.next), head.next.next=head, head.next=null.','Easy','Linked List','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Detect if a linked list has a cycle.','','Floyd''s fast-slow pointer. Slow moves 1, fast moves 2. If they meet, cycle exists.','Tortoise and hare: if fast==null or fast.next==null, no cycle. If slow==fast, cycle.','Easy','Linked List','Amazon','Any',1),
('CODING','Find the middle of a linked list.','','Fast-slow pointer. Fast moves 2, slow moves 1. When fast reaches end, slow is at middle.','Single pass with two pointers. For even-length list, slow stops at second middle.','Easy','Linked List','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Merge two sorted linked lists.','','Compare heads, link smaller, recurse/iterate. Time O(m+n), Space O(1) iterative.','Dummy head approach: while both lists non-empty, append smaller node. Append remaining.','Easy','Linked List','Microsoft','Any',1),
('CODING','Remove the nth node from the end of a linked list.','','Two pointer: advance first pointer n+1 times, then move both. Second pointer is node before target.','Dummy head + two pointers gap of n. When first reaches end, second.next is the node to remove.','Medium','Linked List','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Check if a linked list is a palindrome.','','Find middle, reverse second half, compare with first half, restore (optional).','Slow-fast to find mid, reverse from mid, compare halves, optionally restore.','Easy','Linked List','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Merge K sorted linked lists.','','Use a min-heap (priority queue) of size k. Always extract min, push next from that list. O(Nlogk).','Min-heap: insert head of each list. Pop min, add to result, push that node''s next.','Hard','Linked List','Google','Any',1),

-- Trees
('CODING','Find the height/depth of a binary tree.','','Recursive: height = 1 + max(height(left), height(right)). Base: null node returns -1 or 0.','DFS recursion: max depth = max of left and right subtree depths + 1.','Easy','Trees','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Check if a binary tree is balanced (heights of subtrees differ by at most 1).','','Post-order DFS returning height. Return -1 if unbalanced found in subtree.','Helper returns height or -1 for unbalanced. At each node: if |left-right|>1 return -1.','Medium','Trees','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Lowest common ancestor of two nodes in a BST.','','For BST: if both < root go left, both > root go right, else root is LCA.','BST property: if both values < root.val, recurse left. If both >, recurse right. Else root.','Easy','Trees','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Level order traversal (BFS) of a binary tree.','','Use a queue. Enqueue root. While queue non-empty: dequeue, process, enqueue children.','Queue-based BFS. Track level boundaries by processing queue level by level.','Easy','Trees','Amazon','Any',1),
('CODING','Validate a binary search tree.','','DFS with min/max bounds. At each node, value must be in (min, max) range.','Recursive: valid(node, min, max). Left child: valid(left, min, node.val). Right: valid(right, node.val, max).','Medium','Trees','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Serialize and deserialize a binary tree.','','Pre-order traversal with null markers for serialization. Parse and rebuild for deserialization.','Serialize: preorder with "null" markers. Deserialize: recursive parsing of pre-order string.','Hard','Trees','Google','Any',1),
('CODING','Find the diameter of a binary tree.','','DFS returning height. At each node track max(left+right, current_max). O(n).','Diameter through node = height(left) + height(right). Update global max during postorder.','Medium','Trees','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Path sum - check if root-to-leaf path with given sum exists.','','DFS: subtract node value from target. If leaf and target==0, found.','Recursive: hasPath(node, target) = hasPath(left, t-val) OR hasPath(right, t-val). Leaf check.','Easy','Trees','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Construct binary tree from preorder and inorder traversal.','','Root is preorder[0]. Find root in inorder to split left/right subtrees. Recurse.','Preorder gives root. Root in inorder divides left/right subtrees. Build recursively.','Medium','Trees','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Find all root-to-leaf paths in a binary tree.','','DFS with path tracking. When leaf reached, add path to result.','DFS with list: add node to path, if leaf add to results, recurse children, backtrack.','Easy','Trees','Any',NULL,1),

-- Dynamic Programming
('CODING','Find the nth Fibonacci number using dynamic programming.','','Bottom-up DP: dp[0]=0, dp[1]=1, dp[i]=dp[i-1]+dp[i-2]. Space-optimize with two vars.','Either DP array or two-variable rolling: a,b=0,1; for i in range(n): a,b=b,a+b.','Easy','Dynamic Programming','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Longest increasing subsequence (LIS) length.','','DP: dp[i] = max(dp[j]+1) for all j<i where arr[j]<arr[i]. Or patience sorting O(nlogn).','O(n²): dp[i] = 1 + max dp[j] for j<i, arr[j]<arr[i]. O(nlogn): binary search on tails array.','Medium','Dynamic Programming','Google','Any',1),
('CODING','0/1 Knapsack: given weights and values, maximize value within weight limit.','','DP table: dp[i][w] = max value using first i items with capacity w.','dp[i][w] = max(dp[i-1][w], val[i]+dp[i-1][w-wt[i]]) if wt[i]<=w else dp[i-1][w].','Medium','Dynamic Programming','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Coin change: minimum number of coins to make amount.','','BFS (shortest path) or DP. dp[i] = min coins for amount i. dp[0]=0, rest=infinity.','For each amount a from 1 to target: for each coin c: dp[a] = min(dp[a], 1+dp[a-c]).','Medium','Dynamic Programming','Amazon','Any',1),
('CODING','Longest common subsequence (LCS) of two strings.','','2D DP table. dp[i][j] = LCS of s1[0..i] and s2[0..j].','If chars match: dp[i][j]=dp[i-1][j-1]+1. Else: dp[i][j]=max(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1]).','Medium','Dynamic Programming','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Edit distance (Levenshtein distance) between two strings.','','DP: dp[i][j] = edit distance between s1[0..i] and s2[0..j].','Match: dp[i][j]=dp[i-1][j-1]. Mismatch: dp[i][j]=1+min(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1], dp[i-1][j-1]).','Hard','Dynamic Programming','Google','Any',1),
('CODING','Maximum profit from stock prices with one transaction.','','Track minimum price seen so far. Profit = current price - min price. Track max profit.','Single pass: minPrice=inf, maxProfit=0. For each price: minPrice=min, maxProfit=max(price-minPrice).','Easy','Dynamic Programming','Amazon','Any',1),
('CODING','Decode ways: count ways to decode a digit string to letters (A=1...Z=26).','','DP. dp[i] = ways to decode s[0..i]. Consider single digit and two digits.','dp[i] += dp[i-1] if s[i-1] valid single. dp[i] += dp[i-2] if s[i-2..i-1] valid double (10-26).','Medium','Dynamic Programming','Any',NULL,1),
('CODING','Unique paths in a grid from top-left to bottom-right (only right/down moves).','','DP: dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j] + dp[i][j-1]. Or combinatorics: C(m+n-2, m-1).','dp[i][j] = paths from top + paths from left. Boundary: all 1s. Bottom-right answer.','Easy','Dynamic Programming','Google','Any',1),
('CODING','Jump game: can you reach the last index from first index given max jumps at each position?','','Greedy: track furthest reachable index. If current > furthest, unreachable.','maxReach=0. For i from 0 to n: if i>maxReach return false. maxReach=max(maxReach, i+nums[i]).','Medium','Dynamic Programming','Any',NULL,1),

